[1]
Date: 25 May, 2004
From: Francois Moutou <f.moutou@alfort.AFSSA.FR>

From what I read, the North America or Virginia opossum (_Didelphis
virginiana_) is native in the East, but was introduced to the West of the
Great Plains and the Rocky Mountains.
You can find details in JA Chapman & GA Feldhamer (ed) 1982 - Wild mammals
of North America. The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore and London.
A new edition has very recently been published.
--
Francois Moutou
Epidemiology Unit
AFSSA LERPAZ
BP 67, 94703 Maisons-Alfort Cedex, France
<f.moutou@alfort.AFSSA.FR>
