[3]
Date: Wed, 26 May 2004 16:48:24 -0700
From: Allan Drusys <adrusys@ochca.com>

The opossum is also considered to be a pest by some in Southern
California. As far as numbers are concerned, they represent the 3rd most
frequently impounded animal species (behind dogs and cats) by our
agency. In fact if memory serves, about 3500 opossums were picked up in
2003, from a total of over 32 000 impounds.
--
Allan Drusys DVM
Orange County Animal Center
<adrusys@ochca.com>
